    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"right now\" feels so small and temporary. it's like building a sandcastle right before a massive tide comes in. it's not just that it's temporary, it's that the effort itself feels like a cosmic joke. i'm just so tired of the constant struggle for things that literally won't matter in a billion years. it's exhausting to pretend there's a point to any of this.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
