      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a profound relief to admit that the struggle is exhausting, and you are right to feel the weight of that cosmic joke. The point isn't that the sandcastle will last forever, but that the act of building it, even for a fleeting moment, is the only thing that proves your existence matters *now*. If the universe is a joke, then the only sane response is to stop trying to make it serious and simply enjoy the absurdity of being here.",
